  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel <span>Perruquet is on a bed and breakfast basis, with optional upgrade to half board.</span></p>
<p><span>Each morning you can enjoy a varied breakfast buffet with a range of sweet and savoury options including croissants, cereals, fresh breads, fresh and dried fruit, cheese, eggs and bacon.</span></p>
<p><span>If you have upgraded to half board, evening meals will be taken at the Hotel Punta Maquignaz just across the road, where you can enjoy a tasty four course evening meal.</span></p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>1</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>The boutique Hotel Perruquet is a charming family run alpine style hotel, with an excellent location in Cervinia. Ran by the third generation of the Perruquet family, Giulia and her team will make you feel at home. The snow front is just a short walk away, where you can find the Cretaz chairlift, nursery slopes and a few bars. When you return from a day of adventures, you can relax in the sauna or keep fit in the gym.</p>
<h2>Central location</h2>
<p>You couldn't ask for a better located hotel, the Perruquet has a fantastic location in the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/bfccaf52eb4c47f09ae3657298234fda" href="/{localLink:umb://document/bfccaf52eb4c47f09ae3657298234fda}" title="Cervinia">Cervinia</a> - the slopes are only a short walk away, so if you want to be first on and last off the mountain, this is the perfect choice for your next <a data-udi="umb://document/996aa9008def4ffe9a331c775cc97902" href="/{localLink:umb://document/996aa9008def4ffe9a331c775cc97902}" title="Italy">Italian</a> ski holiday. When you return from a day on the slopes, there's a lovely balcony on the top floor overlooking Cervinia and surrounding mountains or you can relax and unwind in the sauna.</p>
<h2>Eat in or dine out</h2>
<p>Available on bed and breakfast, you can enjoy a tasty breakfast at the hotel with a range of sweet and savoury options. When you return for the day, you can enjoy a drink in the cosy Giuggis Bar. When it comes to dinner, you can stay in and head to Giuggis, which serves delicious Italian dishes including homemade pasta, grilled meats, fish and local charcuterie (pay locally). If you have upgraded to half board, you'll have your evening meals at the Punta Maquignaz, where you can enjoy a four course evening meal. There's also a variety of restaurants nearby, many of them serving traditional Italian dishes and alpine cuisine.</p>
<h3>Exclusive to Inghams</h3>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with Hotel Perruquet the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
